                             Caseload Statistics

   As of December 31, 2000, there were 5,239 Civil cases and 2,969
   Criminal cases (3,842 Criminal Defendants) pending before the seventeen
   district judges of the District Court for the Southern District of
   Texas. 25,913 Bankruptcy main cases were pending before the six judges
   of the Bankruptcy Court for the district. Historical caseload
   information is available.

   The most recent Federal Court Management Statistics, published by the
   Administrative Office of the United States Courts for the twelve month
   period ending September 30, 2000, offer the following information for
   the district:

                                            Southern
                                              Texas
                                                    All Courts
   Total Filings
   per Judgeship                              598      474
   Civil Filings
   per Judgeship                              397      396
   Criminal Filings
   per Judgeship                              201       78
   Pending Cases
   per Judgeship                              395      443
   Weighted Filings
   per Judgeship*                             613      479
   Trials Completed
   per Judgeship                               53       22
   Median Months
   From Filing to Disposition, Civil Cases    9.5      8.2
   Median Months
   From Filing to Disposition, Felony Cases   4.4      6.5
   Median Months
   From Filing to Trial, Civil Cases           18       20
   % Civil Cases
   Over 3 Years Old                           2.0      12.2

   CAPTION: *Weighted Filings are computed according to a formula based on
   average judicial time spent on different types of cases.

   The caseload profile for the last six years is available for this
   district and for all U.S. District Courts. For more information about
   these statistics, see the 2000 Federal Court Management Statistics,
   prepared by the Administrative Office of the United States Courts.

